    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Stonelinks"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d868a1d8-06f9-56f0-8c38-24b7162b5e3b","excerpt":"I came up with this fairly scary bash one liner that will periodically ssh into a machine that you have access to, take a screenshot and copy it back to yourâ€¦","html":"<p>I came up with this fairly scary bash one liner that will periodically ssh into a machine that you have access to, take a screenshot and copy it back to your machine. Just fill in the USER and HOST variables.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\"><span class=\"token environment constant\">USER</span></span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>www-data<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">HOST</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>dev0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token function\">bash</span> -c <span class=\"token string\">\"while [ 0 ]; do ssh <span class=\"token environment constant\">$USER</span>@<span class=\"token variable\">$HOST</span> DISPLAY=:1.0 import -window root /tmp/a.png; date +%s | xargs -I {} scp <span class=\"token environment constant\">$USER</span>@<span class=\"token variable\">$HOST</span>:/tmp/a.png <span class=\"token environment constant\">$USER</span>@<span class=\"token variable\">$HOST</span>-{}.png; sleep 2; done\"</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"SSH Periodic Screenshot","date":"October 08, 2014","description":null}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014-08-19-FCC-data/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"FCC ECFS Comment Dataset"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014-10-10-new-webgl-projects/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"New WebGL Projects"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"d868a1d8-06f9-56f0-8c38-24b7162b5e3b","previousPostId":"dc318929-ecdd-556f-bbb0-f44d98121f7c","nextPostId":"46d1d461-0c17-5ca1-82d3-206f5b5364a5"}},
